1940;;Always a Bride;;American;;Noel M. Smith;;Rosemary Lane, George Reeves, John Eldredge;;comedy;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Always_a_Bride;;Wealthy Alice Bond (Rosemary Lane), dissatisfied with her dishwater-dull fiance Marshall Winkler (John Eldredge), throws him over in favor of Michael Stevens (George Reeves). To make certain that her new beau will be acceptable to her parents, Alice contrives to have Michael enter a mayoral campaign. As election day draws close, criminals complicate matters.[1]